creator: Mighty Networks
descriptionHtml:
LISA is an online community for the maritime industry. A place to gain knowledge, inspiration and support from like-minded professionals and learn how to boost your performance.

* OUR INDUSTRY *

Every day, 80,000 commercial ships transport goods and raw materials, execute projects in ports and offshore sites, and serve the leisure market. Thousands of companies make this possible. LISA connects the people within the companies that design, build, maintain, repair, converse, operate, manage, sell and recycle commercial ships.

* STAY AHEAD OF THE GAME *

The work we do is often challenging and most of what we learn is on the job. With LISA, a whole new source of knowledge, inspiration and support is available at your fingertips. Using state of the art technology, peer-to-peer coaching and in depth industry insights, this community can boost your performance like no other.

* MASTERMINDS *

LISA embodies several Mastermind Groups for you to gain first hand practical knowledge. There are frequent online meetings for Crewing, HQSE, Technical, Operations, IT, Innovation, Marketing & Communication and specific topics upon request. You are able to join any of them, depending on your position and interest. These meetings are fast, valuable and fun, and helps you to be on top of your game.

* MASTERCLASSES *

Occasionally, Mastermind sessions are extended to Masterclasses, where industry experts explain a specific topic in detail. It’s like going to a next level seminar, participating from anywhere you like. We even include online networking, to meet new and interesting people as well. Improve your knowledge and extend your network in a modern way.

* COURSES *

In cooperation with member companies, specific courses are developed and will become available at the end of 2020. These courses are one of a kind and embody practical content, game based learning principles and group learning all in one. Something truly unique in our industry.

* TECHNICAL VLOGS *

Every month, a technical vlog will be released from an equipment supplier. A behind the scenes video with focus on a specific technology and the company involved. Are you working at an equipment supplier and do you want to share something innovative to the industry? Just apply to the community host and we can make it happen.

* INTERVIEWS *

Every month, long interviews with interesting professionals from the network will be released in audio and video. Get inspired by CEO’s, crewing officers, superintendents, R&D experts or IT managers. Do you have something interesting to share as well? Apply to the community host and share your ideas.

* ASK QUESTIONS *

One of the best features in this community is the possibility to ask questions. Questions that take (too) much time to figure out yourself. Challenges that lead to frustration and are impossible to ask Google. So ask the community, find the answers with your peers. They may be able to help you out.

* GROUPS *

Sometimes new business ideas emerge between our community members. LISA supports these initiatives with dedicated groups and project facilitators. If needed, we can even play an active role within the project or help to find the expertise needed.

* OPEN OFFICE HOURS *

There are several tutorials to help you get familiar with LISA. In addition, every week we host open office hours for our members. You can ask live questions, change ideas or just hang out with other community members. These sessions are fun, inspiring and helpful for you to get the most out of this community.

JOIN THE GLOBAL COMMUNITY OF MARITIME PROFESSIONALS

LISA connects you to an international network of maritime professionals. Using state of the art technology, peer-to-peer support and presenting the latest innovative companies, this community can boost your performance like no other.

OUR INDUSTRY
Every day, 80.000 commercial ships transport goods and raw materials, serve the leisure market and execute projects in ports and offshore sites. Thousands of companies make this possible. LISA connects the people within these companies that design, build, supply, maintain, repair, converse, operate, manage, sell and recycle commercial ships.

PARTICIPATE AT INDUSTRY EVENTS FOR FREE
Every week, a series of inspiring Events are available for you to join. For instance ‘Ask me Anything’ sessions with maritime professionals from shipowners, shipyards, equipment suppliers or other interesting organizations. Or Technical Webinars and Online Meetings from innovative companies. Join them and engage with other participants to get the latest industry insights. Most events can be attended directly via the App. Can’t make it live? Then watch replays or sign up for the next one.

VISIT EXHIBITORS AND STAY INFORMED 365 DAYS A YEAR
LISA offers you the possibility to connect with forward thinking Equipment Suppliers, Service Providers, Shipyards, Shipowners, Trade Associations and Maritime Academies. Visit their Exhibitor space where they provide the latest technologies, case-studies and meet-ups. Join the Exhibitor of your liking and stay informed 365 days a year. Gaining knowledge has never been easier; helping you to succeed.

PEER-TO-PEER SUPPORT VIA MASTERMIND GROUPS
If you're working at a Shipowners' Department, like Fleet, Technical, Operations, IT, Crewing, Chartering, Legal or Insurance; you have a challenging job. How would it feel if you can connect with colleagues in an exact similar position, from a different company. To be part of a group where best practices are shared and support is given to overcome daily challenges. A place of trust where you can benchmark your work with others, in a fun and effective way. Welcome to LISA’s Masterminds, available to anyone who fits the criteria.

JOIN US
LISA is growing rapidly and new professionals are discovering it’s potential every day. Join us as well and experience a community that’s welcoming, inclusive, and valuable for everyone. A place where you can connect with like-minded professionals, share knowledge and experiences and help each-other succeed.

Download the LISA Community App, register for free and you're in!

If you are working in commercial shipping, you have a challenging job. Operational issues, maintenance and repair issues, dry-docking issues, spare part issues, travel and logistics issues, manning and training issues, supplier issues, purchase issues, client issues, commercial vetting issues, regulatory compliance issues, budget issues, internal issues………


--- There is no manual how to do it ---

You have to learn from others who already figured out what’s new to you. We reckon you have 80% of your work under control. It’s the other 20% unexpected, new or difficult part that consumes most of your time and energy. The issues where you lack the knowledge or miss the right connections to solve it efficiently and effectively.


--- The good news: there is always someone who has already figured it out ---

You just need to connect with them. Welcome to LISA. LISA connects you to like-minded professionals around the world. People who already know what you don’t know yet. Have experiences with problems that are new to you. And have found practical solutions you are looking for. In return? Just share what you know and help each-other to succeed in our work: making sure ships are sailing.


LISA:

- A trusted global network of maritime professionals

- Connects you with peers, suppliers and clients in an informal and fun way

- Gain knowledge and insights to improve your performance

- Save time, frustration and costly mistakes

- Get unlimited access to the LISA Academy

- Join online and live events on a regular basis

- Available 24/7, 365 days a year, from any place with internet


Why LISA

We believe connecting people in a fun and informal way enables us to better deal with challenges in our daily work. Sharing knowledge and supporting each other will drive to success in the ever-changing shipping industry.
